description.narrative: In 2019, C4D/SBCC research and capacity among national and sub-national universities, local government institutions and partners was strengthened through institutionalisation of curriculum, local participatory planning for child-rights budgeting, and training. Communicating with Communities in Emergency (CwCiE) was institutionalised within the National Standing Orders on Disasters through UNICEF support to partners, a major achievement for the SBCC field in the country. In Cox's Bazar, 81,714 complaints, queries and cases of feedback were recorded by 20 Information Feedback Centres (IFCs) across Rohingya camps and host communities, strengthening accountability to affected populations (AAP). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
